 :dogfoodability-assessment
 {:can-miniforge-implement-this? :yes-with-caveats

  :strengths
  ["Detailed spec with mockups, acceptance criteria, file lists"
   "Clear phase breakdown with dependencies"
   "Existing reference implementations (old dashboard, N5/N9 specs)"
   "Well-defined constraints and architecture"]

  :challenges
  ["Visual design requires aesthetic judgment (Tableau-inspired density)"
   "Chart SVG generation needs geometric calculations"
   "AI integration requires understanding LLM patterns"
   "GitHub integration needs gh CLI expertise"]

  :recommendations
  ["Phase 1-2: Good for miniforge (design system, dashboard overview)"
   "Phase 3-5: May need human guidance (PR/AI integration subtleties)"
   "Phase 6-7: Good for miniforge (polish, charts - algorithmic)"
   "Phase 8-9: Good for miniforge (responsive CSS, tests, docs)"]

  :suggested-approach
  "Start with Phase 1 as a dogfooding test. If miniforge successfully
   implements the design system with good aesthetic judgment and clean
   component architecture, proceed with Phase 2-3. If it struggles with
   visual design decisions, hand-hold through Phase 2, then let it
   continue autonomously for Phase 6-9."}}
